<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-01-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-01-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="714" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d714">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 860d.48/3a</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Counselor for the Department of State</hi>
                                (<persName corresp="#p_PFL1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Polk</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Commercial Adviser
                                of the British Embassy</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_CSR1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Crawford</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-01-12">
                                    <hi rend="italic">January 12, 1918</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear <persName corresp="#p_CSR1">Crawford</persName></hi>: The Secretary is of the opinion that
                            certain definite food supplies for Finland should be allowed to go
                            forward to replace flour which had been purchased by the Finnish Senate
                            and which was subsequently requisitioned here.</p>
                        <p>It will, of course, be necessary to work out safeguards for the delivery
                            of food supplies. For this purpose, and also to obtain the least
                            possible delay, I have asked Mr. <persName>Basil Miles</persName><note n="1" xml:id="d714fn1">Of the Department of State.</note> to confer
                            with you, the Food Administration and the War Trade Board. The <pb facs="0660" n="576" xml:id="pg_576"/> Finnish Commissioner here
                            assures us that Finnish authorities will do everything practicable to
                            cooperate.</p>
                        <p>Sincerely yours,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_PFL1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Frank L. Polk</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>